blog.name: swpromptsandasks
blog.title: StarWars prompts and asks
blog.description: Send me your best (weird, nsfw and cute) prompts and asks for Star wars and if they contain Obi-Wan then hurray for me. Lets see what we can drum up. (I don't write for the last trilogy, apologies)

summary: Hi Moddy 👋, what will happens next in little broken Ben? Will Ben be awake or the council getting involves and maybe Qui Gon get...
question: Hi Moddy 👋, what will happens next in little broken Ben? Will Ben be awake or the council getting involves and maybe Qui Gon get protective with him or the healers throwing the council out, stating their qns can wait until Ben is well?
answer:
Tucking his arms under Ben’s legs and upper back, Qui-Gon lifted the man easily while inwardly grumping about the others weight, shifting the redhead onto the gurney the healer had come with to transport the man.

Ben had yet to wake properly even once through the entire trip though Qui-Gon had managed to at least get his eyes open and help him to the bathroom, something he kind of hoped Ben would not remember though he feared the man would.

But for the most Ben had been comatose with his illness, eyes closed and sweat rolling down his face.

‘But we’re at the temple now,’ Qui-Gon assured himself as he pulled the blanket up over the man and followed the stern apprentice healer, Obi-Wan joining them at the bottom of the ramp as they moved to towards an elevator. ‘He’s going to get better now.’ He reassured himself as he glanced at Ben’s pale face.

Of course when they arrived at the Halls, the entire council was also there as the healers had been duty bound to inform them about the suspected time traveler, a clause that Qui-Gon had not been aware existed but apparently… there was an ancient rule!

And that did support the concept that time travel was possible and also had happened before if there were rules in existence to such beings.

“He does look eerily like young Kenobi, I have to agree that.” Master Plo noted as he leaned back against the wall to watch the healers swarm around the man, the head healer running a diagnostic.

“But different enough to slip under the radar if you didn’t know what to look for.” Sifo agreed, stroking his beard slowly with an intrigued look on his face.

Yaddle and Yoda said nothing, only watched quietly along with the rest and Qui-Gon was relieved that so far none of them seemed to be shaking Ben for answers.

That however was explained when Yoda finally spoke. “Dress and act as a Jedi he does, a Jedi older Kenobi still is obviously.” He croaked out, tapping his claws on his hover platform as Yaddle peered up at him with a gimlet look.

Apparently that was her platform but she lost it to him in a sabbac round.

Or so the rumor went.

Nodding slowly, Qui-Gon rubbed his own beard. “Yes, he meditates and does katas like a Jedi. I didn’t put the clues together back on Typhon but the katas… they are the same as the ones for soresu, meaning that Ben seems to have one point in the future switched out aturu for a more defensive style of dueling.” He explained to the members.

He gained a few surprised gazes that, quick side glances at his rather emotional padawan and some pleased eyes. Obviously they appreciated the idea of Obi-Wan one day taking the more defensive style to him and maybe if one was to really dedicate thought to it, it made sense?

After all, Jedi were not warriors, they fought when necessary but mostly they defended and soresu was the ultimate defense. One could therefor argue it was the ultimate style for a Jedi intent on bringing peace.

“Masters,” They all turned to Master Zukada, the old twi’lek peering at them with a tight look on his face and his lekku twitching. “The patient seems to be waking up in response to the medication currently in his system.”

They all turned on cue at that to look at Ben, watching the man squirm ever so slightly on the bed, lips quivering as if he was speaking and his eyes flickering underneath his eyelids.

Holding his breath, Qui-Gon watched as a small silver of green appeared, Ben opening his eyes slowly to stare at the ceiling for what felt like an eternity before he shifted to look at them.

Yaddle and Yoda said nothing, only watched quietly along with the rest and Qui-Gon was relieved that so far none of them seemed to be shaking Ben for answers.

That however was explained when Yoda finally spoke. “Dress and act as a Jedi he does, a Jedi older Kenobi still is obviously.” He croaked out, tapping his claws on his hover platform as Yaddle peered up at him with a gimlet look.

Apparently that was her platform but she lost it to him in a sabbac round.

Or so the rumor went.

Nodding slowly, Qui-Gon rubbed his own beard. “Yes, he meditates and does katas like a Jedi. I didn’t put the clues together back on Typhon but the katas… they are the same as the ones for soresu, meaning that Ben seems to have one point in the future switched out aturu for a more defensive style of dueling.” He explained to the members.

He gained a few surprised gazes that, quick side glances at his rather emotional padawan and some pleased eyes. Obviously they appreciated the idea of Obi-Wan one day taking the more defensive style to him and maybe if one was to really dedicate thought to it, it made sense?

After all, Jedi were not warriors, they fought when necessary but mostly they defended and soresu was the ultimate defense. One could therefor argue it was the ultimate style for a Jedi intent on bringing peace.

“Masters,” They all turned to Master Zukada, the old twi’lek peering at them with a tight look on his face and his lekku twitching. “The patient seems to be waking up in response to the medication currently in his system.”

They all turned on cue at that to look at Ben, watching the man squirm ever so slightly on the bed, lips quivering as if he was speaking and his eyes flickering underneath his eyelids.

Holding his breath, Qui-Gon watched as a small silver of green appeared, Ben opening his eyes slowly to stare at the ceiling for what felt like an eternity before he shifted to look at them.

trail.content_raw:
Tucking his arms under Ben’s legs and upper back, Qui-Gon lifted the man easily while inwardly grumping about the others weight, shifting the redhead onto the gurney the healer had come with to transport the man.

Ben had yet to wake properly even once through the entire trip though Qui-Gon had managed to at least get his eyes open and help him to the bathroom, something he kind of hoped Ben would not remember though he feared the man would.

But for the most Ben had been comatose with his illness, eyes closed and sweat rolling down his face.

‘But we’re at the temple now,’ Qui-Gon assured himself as he pulled the blanket up over the man and followed the stern apprentice healer, Obi-Wan joining them at the bottom of the ramp as they moved to towards an elevator. ‘He’s going to get better now.’ He reassured himself as he glanced at Ben’s pale face.

Of course when they arrived at the Halls, the entire council was also there as the healers had been duty bound to inform them about the suspected time traveler, a clause that Qui-Gon had not been aware existed but apparently… there was an ancient rule!

summary: The part in Empire Strikes Back when Han decides they’re going into the asteroid field made me laugh today bc Leia and 3PO are...
body: The part in Empire Strikes Back when Han decides they’re going into the asteroid field made me laugh today bc Leia and 3PO are freaking out, but Chewie doesn’t even blink, he’s just like “yeah this is normal, this is the least crazy of the stunts we’ve pulled, sure let’s fly into an asteroid field, no biggie.”
